# Mambo — optional API keys
#
# Mambo runs FULLY OFFLINE with zero keys: the router, pitch tracker, ASR probe,
# rule-based reasoning, and the local LLM planner all work with no network.
# Every key below is OPTIONAL and only upgrades one part of the pipeline.
#
# Setup:  cp .env.example .env   then fill in only the ones you want.
# `.env` is git-ignored — never commit real keys. Keys are read by
# `mambo_lab.settings` (and saved per-session in Mambo Studio's provider chooser).

# --- LLM planner (R1: utterance -> action plan) ------------------------------
# Hosted planner via OpenRouter (has a free tier). Without it, Mambo falls back
# to a local/offline model — the paper reports 0.88 hosted vs 0.86 fully-offline.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# --- Reasoning layer (semantic-verify + sung-lyric dual-decode) --------------
# Used by the gpt-5-mini reasoning calls and the B6 frontier-audio eval. Without
# it, the reasoning layer degrades to the rules-only fallback (still functional).
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# --- Richer speech fixtures + optional STT (ElevenLabs) ----------------------
# `make fixtures-eleven` uses ElevenLabs TTS for higher-fidelity speech fixtures,
# and ElevenLabs Scribe is an optional STT backend. The offline macOS `say`
# backend is the default and needs no key.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# --- Optional alternate planner backend (Anthropic) --------------------------
# Only if you install the `planner` extra and want the Anthropic backend instead
# of OpenRouter/local.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- LoRA training track only (R3, Modal) ------------------------------------
# Needed ONLY to run the fine-tuning experiments on Modal (`finetune/`). Not used
# by the shipping modular pipeline.
MODAL_TOKEN_ID=
MODAL_TOKEN_SECRET=
